BACKUS vs. CARLETON (County Treasurer, Wayne), No. 13937, 99 M., 218.

(Certiorari to Wayne.)

To compel respondent to issue to relator a tax certificate under Sec. 135, Act No. 206, Laws of 1893, without the payment of a fee therefor. The circuit judge granted the writ.

Affirmed February 27, 1894, without costs.
